---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
---
<Layout title="Codeflake | PY: Math">
    <Nav>
		<a href="/">Home</a>
		<a href="/cs">CS</a>
	</Nav>
    <main>
        <h1>Python | Math</h1>
        <p>When writting code we don't use regular symbols like "x" for multiplying. Instead, we use + for making a sum, - for subtracting</p>
        <div class="code">
            print(3 + 3)
        </div>
        <p>When execute this program it'll output 6</p>
        <p>If we want to multiply, we'll use an asterisk (*), and if we want to divide we'll use a forward slash (/).</p>
        <div class="code">
            print(3 * 3)
        </div>
        <p>That would output 9. Then we could get more advanced operations like in real life</p>
        <div class="code">
            print(9 * 9 / (5 + 3))
        </div>
        <div class="next" onclick="location.href = '/python/variables'" style="background-color: wheat; padding: 10px; border-radius: 7px; width: 100%; text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">Next lesson</div>
    </main>
</Layout>
<style>
    main {
        width: 80%;
        max-width: 520px;
        padding: 0 16px;
    }
    main p {
        margin-top: 20px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    .code {
		width: 100%;
		padding: 8px;
		color: #fff;
		background-color: #3f5c6f;
		border-radius: 7px;
		font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
	}
    .code indent {
        margin-left: 15px;
    }
    a {
        text-decoration: none;
        color: #000;
    }
    img {
        object-fit: cover;
        width: 100%;
        height: 200px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 450px) {
        img {
            object-fit: contain;
        }
    }
</style>